()Reference kya hai?
actual object ya value ko copy nahi karte, bas uska address ya location store karte hain.
Example in Java:-
String s1 = "Hello";
String s2 = s1; // s2 ab s1 ka reference hold kar raha hai
Yaha s2 me “Hello” object ka reference” store hai.
Agar s1 ko change karoge (immutable Strings me nahi, mutable objects me), s2 me bhi effect dikh sakta hai.

2️⃣ IAM / Certification Context:-
SailPoint ya CertificationManager me:-
Reference = link kisi object/entity/item ka
Example:-
CertificationEntity entity = manager.getCertificationEntity("user123");
User owner = entity.getOwner(); // owner is a reference to User object
Yaha owner actual User object ka reference hai, copy nahi.
Reference se tu directly owner ka data access ya modify kar sakta hai.

()Example:-
String s1 = "Hello";
String s2 = s1;  // s2 ab s1 ka reference hold kar raha hai
s2 = "World";    // s2 ab ek naya object point kar raha hai
System.out.println(s1); // Hello
System.out.println(s2); // World

()Agar Object Mutable Ho:-
class Person {
    String name;
    Person(String name) { this.name = name; }
}

Person p1 = new Person("Alice");
Person p2 = p1; // p2 bhi p1 object ko reference kar raha hai

p2.name = "Bob"; // mutable object ke field ko change kar diya
System.out.println(p1.name); // Bob
Step 1: p1 aur p2 same object ko reference kar rahe hain
Step 2: p2.name change kiya → p1.name bhi change dikh raha hai

